The Human Rights Commission's Buang Jones says he has been receiving death threats. JOHANNESBURG - The Human Rights Commission's Buang Jones says he has been receiving death threats. He's part of a team investigating alleged corruption and possible human rights violations in Alexandra. READ: Alex residents hope inquiry will yield better living conditions The commission launched a probe following violent service delivery protests. Jones says he's not shaken by the threats. READ: SAHRC launches inquiry into Alex protests "I've received death threats. I'm currently chairing the Alexandra inquiry probing allegations of corruption," he said. The Public Protector has joined forces with the commission to investigate the situation in Alexandra. Alexandra residents brought the township to a standstill last month, demanding better services.